In GitLab by @chaoflow on Aug 10, 2019, 07:25

@sigmavirus24 How do you feel about environment variables providing defaults for CLI options, the way [click](https://click.palletsprojects.com/en/7.x/options/#values-from-environment-variables) is implementing it? Independent of editor integration this could be useful.

I think it would be helpful if flake8 would (at least with ``-v``) print which config file is used.

In GitLab by @sigmavirus24 on Aug 10, 2019, 07:40

@chaoflow I tried this experiment with Twine and it makes it even more difficult to know exactly what's coming from where. Plus it means that defaults for the tool aren't actually defaults and thus `flake8 --help` varies per machine where one or more environment variables are specified.

`-v` can be repeated to show more and more detail. I believe we log the files we visit/find.
